  "title": "A subset of large-scale EEG dataset (India + Tanzania)",
  "description": "A large-scale EEG dataset comprising 7,933 participants from India and Tanzania, collected through field-based research programs with diverse populations ranging from hunter-gatherers to office workers. The dataset demonstrates that nonspecialists can reliably collect high-quality EEG data in non-laboratory settings when provided with appropriate training and structured quality control protocols. Alongside EEG recordings, the dataset includes demographic metadata (age, sex, income) and mental health assessments (Mental Health Quotient scores), enabling investigation of neurophysiological correlates across diverse environmental and socioeconomic contexts.",
  "methods_description": "EEG data were collected by trained research teams across India and Tanzania over a 30-week period using portable EEG equipment. Data quality was maintained through daily automated analysis and feedback using PREP and FASTER methods. The dataset was converted to BIDS format using MNE-BIDS from EDF source files. Participants completed surveys and assessments alongside EEG recording.",
